    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban DRM and protect consumer rights to use technology without restriction",
        "additional_details": "DRM is implemented technically and legally. It limits how people can use technology they purchase.\r\n \r\nIt does not offer copy protection: https://bit.ly/2FklztS\r\n\r\nDRM harms customers & creative industry:\r\n* Render ebooks unreadable https://bbc.in/3huMxMB\r\n* Hold printer users to ransom https://bit.ly/32lqVOb\r\n* Lock publishers into bad deals https://bit.ly/33nHQ1I\r\n* Prohibit screen mirroring https://bit.ly/2Zt1acZ\r\nand impacts technology in many other ways\r\n\r\nThis petition is a call to end this practice",
        "background": "This petition calls on the government to introduce legislation to:\r\n* Ban the inclusion of DRM on on digital media & on physical devices\r\n* Explicitly guarantee the consumer right to remove DRM and use tech & digital media in any way for personal use",
